# Python Styling
* constants are not allowed inside or outside of classes. Prefer the use of a YAML file if it is changeable at runtime. Use internal class variables otherwise. Never have a const value outside fo a class regardless - use a settings file (pydantic-settings)
* Never use import forwarding (import -> re-export). This is an anti-pattern and not allowed
* Question to use ABC or Interface (NotImplementedError)
* Avoid the use of setattr and getattr unless an absolute necessity. Whenever present - ask yourself if it can be done another way. And ask the user if they are create a core/framework code or a generally reusable code
* Make sure all modules have __init__.py in them

# General Style
* Filenames must be the snake case version of the class in the file
* Only one class per file
